body.name: Corsair SP120 Elite, 120mm PWM Hydraulic Bearing Case Fan with CORSAIR AirGuide Technology - Low-Noise, 24.7 dBA, Fan Speeds from 300 RPM - 1,300 RPM, 45.4 CFM, Single Pack - Black
deliveryMessages: FREE delivery Monday, February 19 on orders shipped by Amazon over $35
features: Powerful PWM-controlled fan speeds from 300 RPM up to 1,300 RPM, pushing up to 45.4 CFM of air with 1.23mm-H2O of static pressure.
Utilizes anti-vortex vanes to direct airflow at your hottest components for concentrated cooling, whether used for intake, exhaust, or mounted to a liquid cooling radiator or heatsink.
A hydraulic bearing delivers long-lasting durability and minimal noise, as the 120mm fan blade spins as quietly as 24.7 dBA.
Stops the fan entirely when sent a 0 RPM PWM signal, completely eliminating fan noise.
body.description: The CORSAIR SP120 ELITE 120mm Performance PWM Fan delivers PWM-controlled fan speeds from 300 RPM to 1,300 RPM for powerful cooling where your build needs it most. CORSAIR AirGuide Technology with anti-vortex vanes directs airflow across your hottest components to concentrate your cooling. With an extremely low-noise design and a durable hydraulic bearing, the SP120 ELITE spins as quietly as 24.7 dBa, while pushing up to 43.4 CFM of air with 1.23mm-H2O of static pressure, keeping the airflow up and the decibels down. Support for 0 RPM PWM signals enables the fan to stop completely, eliminating noise entirely for a quietly reliable cooling fan.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I've been using the Corsair SP120 Elite in my PC setup, and it has been a game-changer for cooling efficiency. The CORSAIR AirGuide technology is impressive, directing airflow precisely where it's needed. What I appreciate most is its near-silent operation, thanks to the hydraulic bearing – it's barely noticeable even under heavy load. The build quality is robust, ensuring durability and reliability. Installation was a breeze, fitting perfectly into my case. If you're looking for a high-performance, quiet, and reliable case fan, the SP120 Elite is a fantastic choice, worthy of a five-star rating.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great average fans for replacements!
reviews.reviewText: I've been using this particular 120mm fan for a couple weeks now and honestly it does its job exceptionally well! No RGB, nothing too spectacular, just a working fan that helps balance the air pressure for your system. I am currently using this as an exhaust fan, top side and it doesn't make any noise while spinning in my PC. Perhaps the reason for it being so decently quiet is the fact the average speed is lower than my front and bottom fans, highest it can do is 1300 RPM. Pushing this fan at its top speed made no noticeable noise besides the sound of air being pushed around, or inside the case. I once set this up as a front fan as well and it did great in that position too. So whether you want this as exhaust or intake, I think it won't let you down on either side. It is a fairly simple design and its plug-and-play ready. A great comparison would be the ASUS XF120mm, which I do own, and the only difference between the two is the ASUS is 500 RPM more, and $15 more. Both are great and can work together fine, but the Corsair seems easier to pick here. In the end, I just like this fan and it's still in my case as I make this review.

reviews.reviewTitle: Ventole silenziose e di ottima qualità
reviews.reviewText: Queste ventole sono molto silenziose, il materiale plastico al tatto sembra di ottima qualità, anche dal peso si percepisce che non sono come le classiche ventole di bassa qualità preinstallate nei case.Per montarle è sufficiente avvitarle al case seguendo il classico avvitamento a croce, le viti presenti per ogni ventola sono 4, una per ogni angolo.Qualità prezzo massima per questa fascia di prezzo, le ventole della concorrenza costano molto di più per fornire la stessa qualità di queste ventole, sopratutto parlando di rumore.

Installé sur un boîtier fractal design qui manquait de flux d’air. Comparé a son voisin, le corsair est remarquablement silencieux. Attention ⚠️ : ne faites pas tourner les pales de votre ventilo, cela abîme le roulement à bille et détériore la lubrification.

reviews.reviewTitle: Ventilador que pagas por el rendimiento, no por lucecitas
reviews.reviewText: Si ya te colaron o te diste cuenta de que por el mismo producto con las mismas especificaciones te cobran 100 o 200 € más y ya te has cansado esté ventilador en estupendo, no hace ruido más que si lo pones a 46676554456666444 rpm, no vibra y además de crear un buen flujo de aire es sencillo de instalar...no se en general me parece un muy buen producto...
